President Obama announced his intent to nominate Terence F. Flynn to a key Administration post as a Member of the National Labor Relations Board (NLRB). Flynn currently serves as Chief Counsel to NLRB Board Member Brian Hayes and previously held the same position for former NLRB Board Member Peter Schaumber. He has extensive experience in labor and employment law, having worked at law firms and handled various labor and employment issues, including collective bargaining negotiations, unfair labor practices, ERISA claims, and wage and hour disputes. Flynn holds a B.A. degree from the University of Maryland, College Park, and a J.D. from Washington & Lee University School of Law.